CREATED:20260511T151441Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260511T151441Z
UID:10004143-1781974800-1781980200@buffalobayou.org
SUMMARY:Buffalo Bayou Cruise: History
DESCRIPTION:Look back at Houston’s history while cruising Buffalo Bayou on a 90-minute tour with a local historian. Your guide will share stories of the Allen brothers and provide historical information about the people\, places\, and events along the bayou that helped shape Houston. \n  \nCost \n\nAdults: $40\nChildren: $32 (ages 4-12)\n\n  \nDeparture Location\nAllen’s Landing (1019 Commerce St.) \nWeather permitting. Reservations Required. Children under the age of 4 are not permitted on the pontoon boat. \n  \nPURCHASE TICKETS
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-buffalo-bayou-cruise-history-16-3/
LOCATION:ALLEN’S LANDING\, 1001 Commerce Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, United States
CATEGORIES:History Tours
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Copy-of-AllensLanding-SS-Coffee.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=UTC:20260620T190000
DTEND;TZID=UTC:20260620T210000
DTSTAMP:20260620T080301
CREATED:20260422T200511Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260527T185326Z
UID:10004133-1781982000-1781989200@buffalobayou.org
SUMMARY:Bikes & Bats
DESCRIPTION:Join Buffalo Bayou Partnership and BikeHouston for a batty good time with a bike ride to the Waugh Bridge Bat Colony! \nBring your bike for an evening ride along Buffalo Bayou to the Waugh Drive Bridge\, where you’ll witness an unforgettable sight—more than 300\,000 Mexican free-tailed bats emerging at sunset. Along the way\, bat expert DeAndra Ramsey will share insights about these fascinating and important creatures—affectionately known as “sky puppies.” Spots are limited\, so reserve yours today! \nCost\n$10 \nDuration\n2 hours / 3 miles \nMeeting Location\nThe Water Works in Buffalo Bayou Park (105-B Sabine St) \nTICKETS
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-bikes-and-bats-2/
LOCATION:THE WATER WORKS\, 105 Sabine Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77007\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bat Colony Tours,Bike Tour,Nature Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_0961.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260620T192000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260620T205000
